<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-17296] Multicast option stopOnAggregateException has no effect</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-17296</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The option stopOnAggregateException has no effect. This was added in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-10272&quot; title=&quot;Unexpected behaviour in aggregator if recipient list is processed in parallel&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CAMEL-10272&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CAMEL-10272&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, but since Camel 3.0, the MulticastProcessor method isStopOnAggregateException is no longer called. If any exception is caught in an aggregation strategy, it is set on the original Exchange object and the processing is terminated, whether this option is set or not.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If the option is obsolete, it should be removed and the documentation and test cases should be updated.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
